ENTRY       EC 4.2.1.140                Enzyme
NAME        gluconate/galactonate dehydratase;
            gluconate dehydratase (ambiguous);
            Sso3198 (gene name);
            Pto0485 (gene name)
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Hydro-lyases
SYSNAME     D-gluconate/D-galactonate hydro-lyase
REACTION    (1) D-gluconate = 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-gluconate + H2O [RN:R01538];
            (2) D-galactonate = 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-galactonate + H2O [RN:R03033]
ALL_REAC    R01538 R03033
SUBSTRATE   D-gluconate [CPD:C00257];
            D-galactonate [CPD:C00880]
PRODUCT     2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-gluconate [CPD:C00204];
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-galactonate [CPD:C01216]
COMMENT     The enzyme is involved in glucose and galactose catabolism via the nonphosphorylative variant of the Entner-Doudoroff pathway in Picrophilus torridus [3] and via the branched variant of the Entner-Doudoroff pathway in Sulfolobus solfataricus [1,2]. In vitro it utilizes D-gluconate with 6-10 fold higher catalytic efficiency than D-galactonate [1,3]. It requires Mg2+ for activity [1,2]. cf. EC 4.2.1.6, galactonate dehydratase, and EC 4.2.1.39, gluconate dehydratase.
